## 👤 2. Create Detailed User Personas

---

### 👩‍💼 Persona A: Sarah — HR Administrator

> “I’m tired of jumping between multiple systems to manage one employee.”

#### Who
Senior HR Specialist managing recruitment, onboarding, payroll, and compliance.

- **Tech Literacy:** High  
- **System Dependency:** Very High  

#### Goals
- Manage employee data efficiently  
- Generate reports and insights  
- Ensure smooth HR operations  

#### Behavior
- Uses system extensively (6–8 hours daily)  
- Works with multiple HR tools simultaneously  

#### Devices
- Desktop (Primary – 90%)

#### Pain Points
- Fragmented systems (data spread across tools)  
- Repetitive manual processes  
- Cluttered dashboards  
- Limited reporting flexibility  

#### Opportunity
- Unified system with centralized data  
- Automation of repetitive workflows  
- Advanced reporting capabilities  

---

### 👨‍💼 Persona B: Marcus — Team Manager

> “I need to approve requests instantly without delays.”

#### Who
Mid-level manager responsible for team performance and approvals.

- **Tech Literacy:** Moderate  
- **System Dependency:** Medium  

#### Goals
- Monitor team performance  
- Approve leave requests quickly  
- Conduct performance reviews  

#### Behavior
- Uses system for quick actions daily  
- Uses desktop occasionally for detailed reviews  

#### Devices
- Desktop (reviews)  
- Mobile (approvals & notifications)

#### Pain Points
- Poor mobile experience  
- Too many steps for simple actions  
- Delayed approvals  
- Complex dashboards  

#### Opportunity
- Mobile-first quick actions  
- Simplified workflows  
- One-click approvals  

---

### 👩‍💻 Persona C: Elena — Employee

> “I just want a simple and fast experience.”

#### Who
Individual contributor using the system occasionally.

- **Tech Literacy:** Moderate to High  
- **System Dependency:** Low  

#### Goals
- Apply for leave  
- View payslips and benefits  
- Update personal details  

#### Behavior
- Uses system occasionally (2–3 times/month)  
- Prefers quick interactions  

#### Devices
- Mobile (Primary – 80%)

#### Pain Points
- Complex navigation  
- Too many steps for simple tasks  
- Low engagement with system  
- Lack of self-service features  

#### Opportunity
- Simple and intuitive UI  
- Self-service features  
- Fast access to key actions  

